article.headline: Yale 86, MIT 63
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Jordan Gibson scored 13 points and Ross Morin and Travis Pinick both added 12 to lead Yale over the Massachusetts Institute of Technology 86-63 on Saturday. MIT (7-4) was led by Jimmy Bartolotta with 32 points. Bartolotta, who recently broke the school's all-time scoring mark, also had three steals, three blocks and two assists in the contest. Yale (3-9) scored the final five points of the first half to take 42-29 lead into intermission. The Engineers twice cut into commanding Yale leads early in the second half. But after Bartolotta hit back-to-back 3-pointers to trim the deficit to 50-40, Yale went on a 16-3 run as Gibson had two dunks and a long jumper in the run. Chris Andrews had seven points and five steals and Pinick added eight assists for the Bulldogs.
